<title>USA: NYSE Unavailables -.</title>
<headline>NYSE Unavailables -.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-12-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>The New York Stock Exchange said Monday that Deluxe Corp, Zapata Corp and Iomega Corp were were unavailable for after-hours trading due to news pending.</p>
<p>The exchange also said Corimon SACA, Westmoreland Coal Co and Westmoreland's preferred A stock were not available for trading.</p>
<p>Earlier on Monday, Deluxe said it will take a $140 million to $150 million pre-tax charge in the fourth quarter to complete a restructuing plan.</p>
<p>Zapata said it planned to begin a cash tender offer for up to 15 million shares of its common stock at a price of $4.50 per share.</p>
<p>Iomega said it expected to make staff cuts at its Roy, Utah plants as well as take a $10 million fourth quarter charge.</p>
